						<summary>

						<p>On pillar No. 2 in the compound of the Taluk Office.</p>						

						<p>Undated; written in characters of 12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Mentions Manu (?), Rāghavēndra and Karikala, who may be considered as ancestors of a Telugu-Choḷa family. The name of the donor is lost.</p>						

